!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

coin /kɔɪn/

(coining,coined,coins) 

1. N-COUNT A coin is a small piece of metal which is used as money. 硬币 

例： ...a few loose coins. …几枚零钱。 

2. V-T If you coin a word or a phrase, you are the first person to say it. 创造 (新词语) 

例： Jaron Lanier coined the term 'virtual reality' and pioneered its early development. 加隆·雷尼尔首创“虚拟现实”一词，并率先进行早期开发。 

3. PHRASE You say ' to coin a phrase ' to show that you realize you are making a pun or using a cliché. 套用一个双关语; 套用一句老话 

例： Fifty local musicians have, to coin a phrase, banded together to form the Jazz Umbrella. 套用一句老话，５０位当地的音乐家们联合在一起组成了爵士伞乐队。 

4. PHRASE You use the other side of the coin to mention a different aspect of a situation. 另一方面 

例： On the other side of the coin, there'll be tax incentives for small businesses. 另一方面，会有税收政策激励小型经营者。

</div>

